The paper deals with the problem of placing replicas in a data center or storage area network, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and network information theory (cs.IT). The use of dynamic programming and tree decomposition also suggests a connection to algorithms and complexity (cs.DM). The reliability measure being minimized is also relevant to systems and control (cs.SI), while the focus on data center networks and storage area networks suggests a connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
